    "Part 2 is immediate from part 1.Recall the notion of differentiation of general frames [Blackburn et al., 2001, Def.",
    "5.6].Definition 4.7 (Differentiated Frames).",
    "A partial-state frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ is differentiated iff for all x, y ∈ S: x = y iff for all Z ∈ P, x ∈ Z iff y ∈ Z.By Fact 4.6.2, we have the following.Fact 4.8 (Separativity and Differentiation).",
    "Every separative full possibility frame is differentiated.Another useful fact concerns possibility morphisms to separative frames.",
    "Fact 4.9 (Separativity and Morphisms)."
